You know how to do the answer in this straightforward way. The sum of external forces is minus mg. And that's equal to the mass times the acceleration of a with respect to o. And therefore acceleration of a with respect to o is just minus g. And you could have told me that. That's trivial. If you drop the thing, it accelerates the acceleration of gravity.

