Here's your fictitious force. And that's as if then you've come over here and you've added an additional force on this free body diagram that looks like mg over 4. And now you say the sum of these forces, this is the correction. It's allowing you now to work in this accelerating frame. If do this free body diagram and sum these up, then you will find this expression, which you can solve for n. And you'll get m5 over 4g. In fact, if you stood on the scales, that's what you'd get.

